    {
      "id": "62ab21ddb0321759d3bac9883e1111934c628549",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-17 06:14:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nthis is not right, dt_ref_del is needed here. Probably you encountered issue with named llogs. Can you check if your problem exists with patch http://review.whamcloud.com/6053?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6b869368fa8b684b3360f0e45b58866f2e8ea343",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-04-17 14:32:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Fails\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.4/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/7a186ce4-a768-11e2-b3cc-52540035b04c).  Ran 18 tests.  2 tests failed: conf-sanity, sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "115cf6593e87075ce741cf43aee7bb0bca1b0b91",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-17 16:35:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nhmm, I don't quite understand. if we come to llog destroy we need to destroy the obejct.  and if the object is nnamed llog, then it's supposed to be referenced twice, i think.\n\ncould you explain a bit please?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "32faa5dcd081f1504a725fc968d513d36aa9788a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-17 17:45:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAh, now I understand why the object needs to be refrenced twice. But if the filesystem is upgraded from 1.8, the config log will only have 1 refrence here. I think there are two problem here.\n\n1. ref_del should happen after dt_delete.\n2. one more unnecessary ref_del for upgraded FS.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "96f2dc55bff91ce74712e41bc9175512b8fd8d41",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-17 17:47:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nplease clarify on (1) a bit more",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "370d3ded1c61a9bebddc80b81b0cbef7fe9f7a1a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-18 00:51:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\noh, if you do dt_ref_del first, then it will become an zero nlink file. Then in dt_delete(osd_object_destroy), it will do osd_iget (for trying to delete agent inode, if any), and with 0-link, osd_iget will make it become bad inode.  Then any following operation with bad inode will be affected.  \n\nFor this bug,  some parts of ldiskfs_delete_inode will be skipped, which cause the problem",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "819877285003d130800036f66f7e52a50dd88ceb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-18 16:02:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think this is pretty risky to rely on ordering here. in a month or so some one else working on this or different code may introduce a bug.. just because she is not aware of such a tricky detail of using api. this is not good, imho. instead, we should be able to handle this properly in osd-ldiskfs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1466244c48c5810c32fd893c20018e001841e881",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-18 18:31:33.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
